00:18:46,547 --> 00:18:48,127
I got too excited.

274
00:18:50,219 --> 00:18:51,731
I got excited like an idiot.

275
00:18:54,817 --> 00:18:56,268
I'm so sorry.

276
00:19:01,050 --> 00:19:02,420
I'm okay.

277
00:19:04,326 --> 00:19:05,692
I'm okay with everything

278
00:19:06,685 --> 00:19:09,504
-Even if you don't recognize me...
-I'm not okay.

279
00:19:11,546 --> 00:19:12,952
It's not okay for me.

280
00:19:14,215 --> 00:19:15,048
I...

281
00:19:16,770 --> 00:19:18,309
...want to see you.

282
00:19:20,175 --> 00:19:21,727
I want to recognize you.

283
00:19:27,614 --> 00:19:28,808
So this is what it's like.

284
00:19:30,877 --> 00:19:32,782
Sharing the burdens I have to bear...

285
00:19:34,563 --> 00:19:36,809
... with someone else.

286
00:19:40,997 --> 00:19:42,896
That makes two of us.

287
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:20,552
(Han Segye as Seo Woojoo)

288
00:20:20,686 --> 00:20:22,803
(Han Segye)

289
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:26,559
(Sharp nose and red lips that stands out.)

290
00:20:32,264 --> 00:20:36,602
(Is it Han Segye or not?)

291
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:43,991
(Slightly wavy hair)

292
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:46,078
(The woman from the hospital.)

293
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:53,897
(Updo. Almost didn't recognize.)

294
00:20:53,982 --> 00:20:55,354
(Please help me...)

295
00:21:28,249 --> 00:21:29,082
What's this?

296
00:21:29,755 --> 00:21:30,982
Did you come here to see me?

297
00:21:32,842 --> 00:21:33,675
Yes.

298
00:21:36,625 --> 00:21:37,864
You go ahead.

299
00:21:44,622 --> 00:21:45,455
Why?

300
00:21:45,905 --> 00:21:47,224
You want me to do another good deed?

301
00:21:47,773 --> 00:21:50,109
No. I'm going to do a good deed.

302
00:21:53,863 --> 00:21:54,696
Ta-da.

303
00:21:55,710 --> 00:21:57,656
I figured you haven't had a cake yet.

304
00:21:58,178 --> 00:21:59,783
You skip meals often.

305
00:22:00,220 --> 00:22:01,516
But it's your birthday.

306
00:22:14,357 --> 00:22:16,704
I brought one candle to make it simple.

307
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:31,683
I'll skip the song
since you won't like it.

308
00:22:32,066 --> 00:22:33,554
Blow the candles out.

309
00:22:40,531 --> 00:22:41,683
I got...

310
00:22:43,909 --> 00:22:45,397
...flowers for my birthday.

311
00:22:47,902 --> 00:22:49,466
And those flowers mean...

312
00:22:50,276 --> 00:22:52,060
"Happiness surely to come."

313
00:22:56,392 --> 00:22:58,611
I know I shouldn't do this.

314
00:22:59,202 --> 00:23:02,195
But if there's my share of happiness...

315
00:23:05,340 --> 00:23:06,777
...I think it would be you.

316
00:23:08,446 --> 00:23:09,279
Pardon?

317
00:23:11,172 --> 00:23:12,960
I like you.

318
00:23:19,312 --> 00:23:20,605
It seems like I do.

319
00:23:28,235 --> 00:23:29,270
I...

320
00:23:30,863 --> 00:23:32,337
I'm always kind.

321
00:23:33,201 --> 00:23:34,895
So you might misunderstand.

322
00:23:35,963 --> 00:23:39,109
But I love God.

323
00:23:40,086 --> 00:23:42,607
I want to follow
the footsteps of the Lord.

324
00:23:48,418 --> 00:23:49,322
I understand.

325
00:23:52,057 --> 00:23:56,735
I've been through that
a lot since elementary school.

326
00:23:57,534 --> 00:23:59,159
You don't have to blame yourself...

327
00:23:59,243 --> 00:24:00,791
You said don't like a bad person.

328
00:24:01,662 --> 00:24:02,495
Then...

329
00:24:06,097 --> 00:24:07,713
...why are you so bad to me?

330
00:24:16,850 --> 00:24:18,057
Also...

331
00:24:18,584 --> 00:24:19,892
I don't like cake.

332
00:25:14,034 --> 00:25:15,981
I don't have a religion...

333
00:25:16,410 --> 00:25:18,133
...but I'm in a hurry.

334
00:25:19,681 --> 00:25:21,787
Please give this man up to me.

335
00:25:23,473 --> 00:25:26,258
If you do, I'll make
big donations to the church.

336
00:25:26,974 --> 00:25:30,662
Whatever amount you're thinking,
it'll be a lot more than that.

337
00:25:32,194 --> 00:25:33,027
I'm...

338
00:25:33,601 --> 00:25:35,314
...trying to negotiate with you.

339
00:25:35,819 --> 00:25:37,970
So please...

340
00:25:40,152 --> 00:25:41,977
...give me that man, Ryu Eunho.

341
00:25:44,193 --> 00:25:46,779
I look forward to hearing
good news from you.

342
00:26:05,707 --> 00:26:07,599
Why am I such a mess?

343
00:26:08,822 --> 00:26:10,500
Why am I such a mess?

344
00:26:10,585 --> 00:26:13,117
Why are you two such a mess?

345
00:26:14,408 --> 00:26:16,792
Why? What's up with you guys?

346
00:26:16,877 --> 00:26:19,027
Why do I regret later all the time?

347
00:26:19,887 --> 00:26:21,547
I should've done better.

348
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:24,755
I should've tried to do better.

349
00:26:25,275 --> 00:26:26,485
Yeah...

350
00:26:27,303 --> 00:26:29,656
Why do I always regret it later?

351
00:26:30,475 --> 00:26:32,456
I should've done less.

352
00:26:32,812 --> 00:26:35,397
I should've tried to do less.

353
00:26:35,482 --> 00:26:37,606
What the hell is this?

354
00:26:37,978 --> 00:26:39,820
Is this a secret code game?

355
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:42,434
(Mom)

356
00:26:44,706 --> 00:26:45,731
Why don't you take it?

357
00:26:45,997 --> 00:26:48,790
It's not that I don't want to, I can't.

358
00:26:49,339 --> 00:26:51,780
And what's the point?
She'll repeat the same thing again.

359
00:26:52,178 --> 00:26:53,175
What thing?

360
00:26:53,304 --> 00:26:55,468
"Get married," or whatever.

361
00:26:55,902 --> 00:26:56,831
Already?

362
00:26:57,143 --> 00:26:57,976
No way.

363
00:26:59,929 --> 00:27:02,721
Are you saying that as my friend
or as the CEO?

364
00:27:03,222 --> 00:27:04,723
Both.

365
00:27:06,943 --> 00:27:09,220
Just get it over with.

366
00:27:09,449 --> 00:27:11,396
Do it while I'm still here.

367
00:27:11,487 --> 00:27:14,533
Once I enter the seminary,
I won't be able to attend your wedding.

368
00:27:15,097 --> 00:27:16,439
You're really going this time?

369
00:27:16,523 --> 00:27:18,153
I've already submitted
the application form....

370
00:27:18,515 --> 00:27:19,348
...yesterday.

371
00:27:19,850 --> 00:27:20,820
-What!
-What!

372
00:27:21,153 --> 00:27:22,338
Why tell us that now?

373
00:27:22,422 --> 00:27:23,483
Please don't move.

374
00:27:23,567 --> 00:27:25,844
She said you can't move.

375
00:27:26,028 --> 00:27:27,497
I can move my foot, right?

376
00:27:29,283 --> 00:27:31,418
Now this is like a comedy.

377
00:27:31,503 --> 00:27:34,067
You're one to talk.
Your life's a soap opera.

378
00:27:34,268 --> 00:27:35,236
I can move my foot, right?

379
00:27:35,321 --> 00:27:36,594
Your nails are done..

380
00:27:38,175 --> 00:27:40,084
Why is yours done now?

381
00:27:42,790 --> 00:27:43,623
Who's this?

382
00:27:45,183 --> 00:27:46,099
Hello?

383
00:27:46,184 --> 00:27:48,073
Are you the guardian of Han Sookhee?

384
00:27:50,695 --> 00:27:51,528
What?

385
00:28:10,137 --> 00:28:10,986
Mom.

386
00:28:11,941 --> 00:28:12,774
Hey.

387
00:28:14,047 --> 00:28:14,960
You're here.

388
00:28:15,850 --> 00:28:16,683
Mom...

389
00:28:17,877 --> 00:28:18,884
What are you doing here?

390
00:28:20,147 --> 00:28:21,624
Don't you have work today?

391
00:28:21,859 --> 00:28:23,936
I didn't think you would come
because you're busy.

392
00:28:24,263 --> 00:28:25,875
What are you doing here?

393
00:28:26,253 --> 00:28:28,173
Why are you in the hospital?

394
00:28:31,332 --> 00:28:32,442
Pancreatic cancer is...

395
00:28:33,049 --> 00:28:34,863
...difficult to be found
in the early stage.

396
00:28:36,016 --> 00:28:39,891
The early symptoms are
similar to stomachaches.

397
00:28:40,122 --> 00:28:41,876
When the symptoms start showing...

398
00:28:42,392 --> 00:28:44,690
... it means the cancer's
already advanced.

399
00:28:45,713 --> 00:28:48,800
When she came to the emergency room...

400
00:28:49,428 --> 00:28:51,482
...she was already aware
about her cancer.

401
00:28:52,851 --> 00:28:54,815
What are the chances
of her pulling through?

402
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,398
In your mother's case...

403
00:28:59,622 --> 00:29:01,298
... it's less than 10 percent.

404
00:29:06,695 --> 00:29:07,629
Then...

405
00:29:09,346 --> 00:29:10,418
How...

406
00:29:17,172 --> 00:29:18,862
How long does she have?

407
00:29:21,437 --> 00:29:22,667
About one month...

408
00:29:23,772 --> 00:29:25,065
... at best.

409
00:29:35,829 --> 00:29:36,954
No way...

410
00:29:41,575 --> 00:29:43,215
It can't be...

411
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:03,149
Mom.

412
00:30:03,695 --> 00:30:04,528
Yeah?

413
00:30:05,313 --> 00:30:06,479
What's that for?

414
00:30:07,092 --> 00:30:10,342
For Kingkang to wear
when the weather gets cold.

415
00:30:14,433 --> 00:30:15,524
Do you...

416
00:30:16,466 --> 00:30:18,421
...have to make that right now?

417
00:30:19,172 --> 00:30:21,155
If not now, then when?

418
00:30:24,773 --> 00:30:26,139
Doesn't it make you angry?

419
00:30:27,307 --> 00:30:28,941
Don't you feel wronged?

420
00:30:36,127 --> 00:30:37,075
I am angry.

421
00:30:37,914 --> 00:30:38,874
I do feel wronged.

422
00:30:41,231 --> 00:30:43,250
But it's just one of those things.

423
00:30:44,533 --> 00:30:45,462
Do you know...

424
00:30:47,756 --> 00:30:49,431
...what I was doing?

425
00:30:51,855 --> 00:30:53,385
Before I got here...

426
00:30:55,342 --> 00:30:57,227
...I was getting nail care.

427
00:30:59,989 --> 00:31:03,751
When you were on the floor in agony...

428
00:31:06,713 --> 00:31:08,967
...I was getting my stupid nails done.

429
00:31:10,929 --> 00:31:11,779
Segye...

430
00:31:11,864 --> 00:31:14,374
I got your call when I was
at the nail shop.

431
00:31:16,848 --> 00:31:17,781
I...

432
00:31:21,281 --> 00:31:22,887
... didn't even know you were like this.

433
00:31:24,570 --> 00:31:27,052
I thought you were going to nag again.

434
00:31:30,368 --> 00:31:32,324
So I didn't pick up your call.

435
00:31:35,088 --> 00:31:36,895
It's okay.

436
00:31:37,371 --> 00:31:38,562
You didn't know.

437
00:31:38,646 --> 00:31:41,245
So why did you keep me in the dark?

438
00:31:45,846 --> 00:31:48,494
Why didn't you say anything
and make me a bad daughter?

439
00:31:49,611 --> 00:31:50,713
How much would I...

440
00:31:53,176 --> 00:31:57,110
How much would I resent myself
if that was the last moment?

441
00:31:59,562 --> 00:32:00,935
How could I...

442
00:32:03,886 --> 00:32:06,342
How could I live with myself?

443
00:32:07,882 --> 00:32:08,902
I'm sorry.

444
00:32:10,433 --> 00:32:11,543
I just...

445
00:32:12,273 --> 00:32:13,106
I didn't...

446
00:32:14,387 --> 00:32:16,278
...want you to be heartbroken.

447
00:32:21,445 --> 00:32:23,120
You're only thinking about me again.

448
00:32:24,870 --> 00:32:27,957
You and I both make it all about me.

449
00:32:28,412 --> 00:32:32,217
Why did you spend your entire life
thinking about me?

450
00:32:34,473 --> 00:32:36,300
Because you're my daughter.

451
00:32:37,854 --> 00:32:40,377
You're my only child.

452
00:33:27,006 --> 00:33:29,058
The weather today is so nice.

453
00:33:32,115 --> 00:33:33,036
Yes it is.

454
00:33:33,894 --> 00:33:35,134
The weather is...

455
00:33:35,915 --> 00:33:36,866
...so nice.

456
00:33:39,583 --> 00:33:41,119
Don't get sick.

457
00:33:43,489 --> 00:33:45,487
I like you.

458
00:33:47,434 --> 00:33:49,620
It's not because you're with my daughter.

459
00:33:50,247 --> 00:33:52,272
I just like you.

460
00:33:52,842 --> 00:33:56,837
So I hope you stay healthy.

461
00:33:58,391 --> 00:34:00,496
I hope you have a happy life.

462
00:34:06,618 --> 00:34:08,169
Thank you for the presents.

463
00:34:09,272 --> 00:34:10,865
It wasn't much.

464
00:34:12,571 --> 00:34:14,371
I just wanted to receive gifts.

465
00:34:15,299 --> 00:34:18,030
I thought I won't get another chance.

466
00:34:18,931 --> 00:34:20,892
So I accepted them
even though I shouldn't have.

467
00:34:21,363 --> 00:34:22,522
You did good.

468
00:34:28,158 --> 00:34:29,824
When I let go of her hand...

469
00:34:30,807 --> 00:34:32,428
...please hold it for me.

470
00:34:34,734 --> 00:34:35,907
I've passed on...

471
00:34:36,396 --> 00:34:37,842
...the baton over to you now.

472
00:34:39,474 --> 00:34:40,307
Yes.

473
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:48,160
Is Segye's movie almost done filming?

474
00:34:48,869 --> 00:34:49,921
We should...

475
00:34:50,506 --> 00:34:52,082
...go watch the movie together.

476
00:34:53,688 --> 00:34:55,462
Will you buy the popcorn?

477
00:34:56,376 --> 00:34:57,563
I'll buy the tickets...

478
00:34:57,823 --> 00:34:59,368
...and the drinks.

479
00:35:00,161 --> 00:35:03,828
I'll be happy to go since my
son-in-law will treat everything.

480
00:35:15,727 --> 00:35:18,847
Even though we knew
that we cannot keep them...

481
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:21,591
...we still made promises.

482
00:35:23,038 --> 00:35:24,584
Is it because we want to be sadder?

483
00:35:25,599 --> 00:35:27,264
Or because we want to be less sad?

484
00:35:29,199 --> 00:35:30,776
I'm not sure about that.

485
00:35:31,782 --> 00:35:32,615
But...

486
00:35:33,563 --> 00:35:35,270
...maybe it's because...

487
00:35:35,901 --> 00:35:37,636
...we hope to keep that promise.

488
00:35:39,354 --> 00:35:40,444
Mom, look over here.

489
00:35:40,528 --> 00:35:42,979
Death may seem far away...

490
00:35:43,197 --> 00:35:45,143
...but it's always near us.

491
00:35:45,538 --> 00:35:47,201
It's actually a video.

492
00:35:47,286 --> 00:35:50,749
You should've told me.
I didn't even wear lipstick.

493
00:35:50,833 --> 00:35:52,469
You're pretty without it anyway.

494
00:35:52,585 --> 00:35:54,163
I look prettier when I apply lipstick.

495
00:35:54,247 --> 00:35:56,598
Sure you do.

496
00:35:56,683 --> 00:35:59,057
-Zooming in...
-Stop recording!

497
00:36:01,023 --> 00:36:03,133
When we become aware of its existence...

498
00:36:03,646 --> 00:36:05,324
...it's already right next to us.

499
00:36:06,240 --> 00:36:07,850
And we can't run away from it.

500
00:36:10,594 --> 00:36:14,096
It's so cute and adorable.

501
00:36:14,180 --> 00:36:16,174
It's way too cute.

502
00:36:17,165 --> 00:36:18,420
That goes without saying.

503
00:36:18,658 --> 00:36:21,046
I don't make things that aren't cute.

504
00:36:21,153 --> 00:36:24,347
Sure, of course you don't.

505
00:36:25,169 --> 00:36:26,751
It's a gift for Kingkang...

506
00:36:27,068 --> 00:36:32,187
...so she can live with you
for a long time without catching cold.

507
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:37,033
I have to tell her.

508
00:36:43,848 --> 00:36:45,319
I love you, Mom.

509
00:36:57,386 --> 00:36:58,614
Mom, I love you.

510
00:36:58,699 --> 00:37:01,991
-I love you.
-Love you, Mom.

511
00:37:02,712 --> 00:37:05,911
-I love you a hundred times.
-Mommy loves you too.

512
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:19,142
I love you, Mom.

513
00:37:34,935 --> 00:37:36,570
Mom, I love you.

514
00:37:42,773 --> 00:37:44,230
Because time always...

515
00:37:45,001 --> 00:37:47,172
...passes by faster than we think.

516
00:37:48,192 --> 00:37:50,568
I'll be out of the country for a while.

517
00:37:50,705 --> 00:37:52,621
-I'm sorry.
-Enjoy your trip.

518
00:39:08,536 --> 00:39:09,749
Already?

519
00:39:16,972 --> 00:39:17,840
Why...

520
00:39:21,137 --> 00:39:23,316
Why now?

521
00:39:25,991 --> 00:39:27,135
Why...?

522
00:39:49,142 --> 00:39:50,221
Segye.

523
00:39:50,561 --> 00:39:52,464
Don't worry too much.

524
00:39:53,788 --> 00:39:55,360
You don't have to be sorry.

525
00:39:55,929 --> 00:39:56,825
Okay.

526
00:40:02,776 --> 00:40:03,801
Ma'am.

527
00:40:08,162 --> 00:40:09,297
Where's Segye?

528
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:17,442
She's filming right now.
It was too important for her to miss.

529
00:40:19,210 --> 00:40:22,232
My daughter's a star. It is what it is.

530
00:40:23,116 --> 00:40:26,550
She'll be here any minute.

531
00:41:12,547 --> 00:41:14,072
Time's passing by.

532
00:41:18,279 --> 00:41:20,963
Night falls, morning rises.

533
00:41:21,208 --> 00:41:22,360
Noon comes around...

534
00:41:22,771 --> 00:41:25,543
â€¦ then evening and night falls again.

535
00:41:37,093 --> 00:41:39,158
Heartbreaking days...

536
00:41:40,145 --> 00:41:42,097
...passes by meaninglessly.

537
00:41:46,710 --> 00:41:47,774
When you get sick...

538
00:41:49,076 --> 00:41:50,575
...I feel like it's all my fault.

539
00:41:51,513 --> 00:41:54,579
I feel like you're taking punishment
for my wrongdoings.

540
00:42:00,448 --> 00:42:01,281
Please...

541
00:42:02,075 --> 00:42:05,661
If there is God, please help
me change as soon as possible.

542
00:42:06,115 --> 00:42:08,526
Even if it's just one day earlier...

543
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:17,902
(Uncle)

544
00:42:25,708 --> 00:42:26,848
Hello?

545
00:42:28,171 --> 00:42:29,090
Your voice...

546
00:42:29,352 --> 00:42:30,451
...is different.

547
00:42:31,383 --> 00:42:33,080
I've changed again...

548
00:42:33,581 --> 00:42:34,769
...in the midst of everything.

549
00:42:35,552 --> 00:42:36,453
I'm sorry...

550
00:42:37,256 --> 00:42:38,971
...for not being there for you.

551
00:42:41,056 --> 00:42:43,617
You're keeping me company now.

